A garden list of other stuff that is managable: Runny nose, constipation, indigestion, trouble staying asleep, blah, blah. But Im tanking through it.

-JdnKUdeDE6kXjOeBQmD.text:
Old inhabitants tell how, in a certain Nevada camp, the news went abroad early in the morning that a woman was come! The miners had seen a calico dress hanging out of a wagon down at the camping ground -- sign of emigrants from over the great plains. Everybody went down there, and a shout went up when an actual bona fide dress was discovered fluttering in the wind! The male emigrant was visible. The miners said:

Fetch her out!

He said: Its my wife, gentlemen---she is sick---we have been robbed of money, provisions, everything, by the Indians---we want to rest.

Fetch her out! Weve got to see her!

But gentlemen, the poor thing, she---

FETCH HER OUT!

He fetched her out, and they swung their hats and sent up three rousing cheers, and they crowded around and gazed at her, and touched her dress, and listened to her voice with the look of men who listened to a memory rather than a present reality---and then they collected twenty-five hundreds dollars in gold and gave it to the man, and swung their hats again, and gave three more cheers, and went home satisfied.

So for Collins, picking a team comes down mostly location and fit. A native of Baton Rouge, he committed to LSU early in the recruiting process for the Class of 2011 largely because it was home. USC recruited Collins, a process that started when Pete Carroll was still the coach of the Trojans. By the time Collins took his official visit to USC, Carroll was coach of the Seahawks. Reports at the time indicated that Collins liked USC but never seriously considered going anywhere other than LSU, in part due to desiring to stay home.

Many figure that could be a big factor for Collins now as he chooses a team, and one reason that speculation over which teams he might be interested in has centered largely on those in the south  Miami, Tampa Bay and Dallas, to name three.

Collins, though, was reported to have met with Buffalo coach Rex Ryan on Tuesday.

He was also reported to have visited the Cowboys on Wednesday, with those reports indicating that Dallas put a pretty heavy sales job on Collins. Its been reported, though, that Collins wants to make more trips. UPDATE  He is reported to be visiting Miami Thursday.
